{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI12ViewModifierP"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The top toolbar (aka ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"navigation bar","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" on iOS and iPadOS 18 and lower) sits at the top of the screen and provides contextual information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and controls related to the current view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It typically displays the page title, and may include navigation actions such as “Back” or “Close” as well as supplementary actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It can contains leading and trailing actions.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSToolBarTop"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"toolBarTop(_:hasLargeTitle:subtitle:leadingItems:trailingItems:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"  View helper applies a SwiftUI toolbar configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Appearances","text":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With Liquid Glass \/ iOS 26+ the OS will change the rendering of the toolbar items depending to the context:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The OS can group the items of same types in one group with kind of rectangle (e.g. views with menus)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"But for buttons items they will remain isolated"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The placement of the title can be leading or centered depending to the length of the text","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The text can be truncated if there is not enough remaining space","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The OS can apply another style for the back button","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Without Liquid Glass \/ iOS 18 and lower, the OS won’t change that much the style of the toolbar items, Items won’t be visually grouped.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Globaly the appearence of the * navigation bar* elements is changed by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsNavigationBarAppearance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"helper of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" that must be applyed on the root view of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStack"},{"type":"text","text":" for example."}]},{"text":"Technical constraints","anchor":"Technical-constraints","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To be sure for iOS 18 and lower the back buttton and text have the good color, in your main view apply the following accent color:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    struct AppMainView: View {","        var body: some View {","            ContentView()","                .accentColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","        }","    }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Platform consid